gomodel:SYNGO_2161  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Electron micrographs showing that Kv4.2 is differentially expressed at putative inhibitory and excitatory synapses in mouse primary visual cortex\"\n- \"A, Extrasynaptic localization of Kv4.2 immunoperoxidase labeling (arrows) at an asymmetric synapse onto a thin dendrite (D)\"\n- \"D, Extrasynaptic localization of Kv4.2 (arrows) at an asymmetric synapse onto GABA immunogold (black dots)-labeled dendrite. E, Synaptic localization of Kv4.2 at a symmetric synapse (AT2) onto a pyramidal cell soma (P). Notice that Kv4.2 is contained in the postsynaptic membrane associated with the synaptic cleft, \"\n\nFig.8: \"Electron micrographs showing differential localization of Kv4.2 and Kv4.3 at GABAergic and non-GABAergic synapses in mouse primary visual cortex. A, Kv4.2 immunoperoxidase (arrows and arrowheads) expression in a GABA immunogold (black dots)-labeled section. Notice that Kv4.2 (arrows) is expressed in the spine (Sp) membrane but is excluded from the asymmetric synapse formed by a non-GABAergic Gray type 1 axon terminal (AT1). In contrast, Kv4.2 is expressed at a symmetric synapse formed by GABA immunogold-labeled Gray type 2 axon terminal. B, C, Postsynaptic localization of Kv4.3 immunoperoxidase labeling (arrows) at symmetric synapses formed by GABAergic (black dots) Gray type 2 axon terminals onto dendrite (D) and perikaryon (P). \"\n\nNote:\n- Depending on the synapse KCND2 / Kv4.2 is present in the extrasynaptic or synaptic plasma membrane.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Mice were anesthetized and perfused as described for light microscopic experiments ... \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2161" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

